            "id": "ec20b111adbe42dfa812b",
            "questionText": "An engineer is designing a solar water heater using a black metal plate exposed to sunlight to heat water flowing through pipes. The plate has a surface area of $!$2 \\; m^2$!$ and reaches a temperature of $!$80^\\circ C$!$ on a sunny day. Assuming the plate behaves as a perfect black body, calculate the radiated intensity in $!$W/m^2$!$. First convert the Celsius temperature to Kelvin. Use the Stefan-Boltzmann constant, $!$\\sigma = 5.67 \\times 10^{-8} \\;W\\,m^{-2}\\,K^{-4}$!$.",
            "imageText": "",
            "steps": [
                {
                    "id": "7cc0790a23914843a9819",
                    "stepText": "Let's start by identifying the correct formula for converting a temperature from Celsius to Kelvin. Please select the appropriate conversion expression.",
                    "stepText2": "",
                    "stepImage": "",
                    "stepSolveAnswer": [
                        ""
                    ],
                    "stepSolveAnswerUnits": "",
                    "stepConcepts": [
                        "c6bf6d0a-28fa-49be-b9a9-78e246403dae",
                        "9c067b29-5b92-4476-b2d5-d21d8461c543"
                    ],
                    "options": [
                        {
                            "optionText": "$!$T_K = T_C + 273$!$",
                            "optionImage": "",
                            "isCorrect": true
                        },
                        {
                            "optionText": "$!$T_K = T_C - 273$!$",
                            "optionImage": "",
                            "isCorrect": false
                        },
                        {
                            "optionText": "$!$T_K = T_C \\times 273$!$",
                            "optionImage": "",
                            "isCorrect": false
                        }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id": "df3f3b01ef2f4da084cdb",
                    "stepText": "Great! Now, using the formula you selected, convert the temperature $!$80^\\circ C$!$ to Kelvin by performing the appropriate calculation.",
